<P>A SERMON, IN WHICH THE UNION OF THE COLONIES IS CONSIDERED AND RECOMMENDED; AND THE SAD CONSEQUENCES OF DIVISIONS ARE REPRESENTED. DELIVERED ON THE PUBLIC THANKSGIVING. NOVEMBER SIXTEENTH, 1775.</P>
<P>By ROBERT ROSS, A. M. Pa&s;tor of the CHURCH of CHRIST in <HI>Stratfield.</HI></P>
<Q>&mdash;<HI>And the fear of the Lord fell on the People, and they came out with</HI> ONE CONSENT.
<BIBL>1 Sam. xi. 7.</BIBL></Q>
<P>NEW-YORK: Printed by JOHN HOLT, in WATER STREET, near the Coffee-Hou&s;e. M,DCC,LXXVI.</P>
</DIV1>
