<PB REF="015070_0002_0F95A829B8059550">
<HEAD>ADVERTISEMENT.</HEAD>
<P><HI>THE following Sermon was compo&s;ed in ha&s;te for a common congregation in the country, without any expectation of its being de&s;ired to be publi&s;hed. But many of my hearers were very earne&s;t in their reque&s;ts that it might be printed, to which I have yielded. I have not had lei&s;ure to tran&s;cribe and poli&s;h it, and if I had, perhaps &s;hould not take the pains, &s;ince the drudgery of tran&s;cribing would put me to more trouble, than it would afford plea&s;ure or advantage to the rea|ders. The &s;entiments and rea&s;onings are expre&s;&s;ed in a plain manner, and if they are ju&s;t, this plain|ne&s;s will not be di&s;agreeable; but if they are wrong, the Author has no de&s;ire that the embel|li&s;hments of &s;tile &s;hould recommend them.&mdash;The candid reader will make the favourable allow|ances, which are u&s;ually reque&s;ted for ha&s;ty pro|ductions.</HI></P>
</DIV1>
